                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d573">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.51/505a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">at Nanking</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-03T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 3, 1937—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>210. This afternoon certain American newspapers feature a United Press article
                    with headline “U. S. Banks Helping Finance Jap War”. The simple facts, according
                    to the Department’s understanding, are that certain American banks have
                    continued ordinary financial transactions which consist of granting credits to
                    Yokohoma Specie Bank against gold now in transit to the United States and
                    against United States bonds.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
